Step 2 — Properties tab values
In the New table dialog, on the Properties tab:
Display name:
BU Org Unit Mapping
Description:
Maps LeanIX Org Unit strings to normalized Business Units. Flow 1 writes new entries when it encounters unmapped org unit strings; admins assign Target BU to resolve them.
Plural name: auto-fills to BU Org Unit Mappings — leave it.
Expand Advanced options:
Schema name: verify auto-fills to BUOrgUnitMapping (full logical becomes pei_BUOrgUnitMapping)
Type: Standard
Record ownership: User or team
Enable for... check these:

Auditing
Activities
Notes
Connections

(Leave the other Enable-for checkboxes at default.)
⚠️ Don't click Save yet — set Primary column on the next tab first.

Step 3 — Primary column tab
Click into the Primary column tab.
Display name:
Org Unit Variant
Description:
The verbatim Org Unit string as exported from LeanIX. Used as the lookup key when Flow 1 resolves applications to Business Units. Must be unique across the table.
Data type: Single line of text
Expand Advanced options:
Schema name: verify auto-fills to OrgUnitVariant
Maximum character count:
200
Required: Business required

Step 4 — Save the table
Click Save at the bottom. Wait 15–30 seconds for the table to finish creating; you'll land on the table editor.

Step 5 — Add column: Target BU (lookup)
In table editor → Columns area → + New column.
Display name:
Target BU
Description:
The Business Unit this Org Unit string maps to. Null when status is Unresolved.
Data type: Lookup
Related table: Business Unit
Required: Optional
Under Advanced options, set the Schema name to:
targetbu
Click Save.

Step 6 — Add column: Status (choice)
Click + New column.
Display name:
Status
Description:
Whether this org unit string has been mapped to a BU, deliberately ignored, or is still unresolved.
Data type: Choice
Sync this choice with: New choice
Choice items — add exactly three, in this order:
Item 1:

Label: Unresolved
Value: 890920000

Item 2:

Label: Mapped
Value: 890920001

Item 3:

Label: Ignored
Value: 890920002

Default choice: Unresolved
Required: Business required
Under Advanced options, manually edit the Schema name to:
mappingstatus
(So full logical becomes pei_mappingstatus, not pei_status.)
Click Save.

Step 7 — Add column: Notes
Click + New column.
Display name:
Notes
Description:
Admin notes about this mapping (e.g. why it was ignored, ambiguity flags, who to ask).
Data type: Multiple lines of text
Format: Text (plain — NOT Rich text)
Maximum character count:
2000
Required: Optional
Click Save.

Step 8 — Add column: First Seen
Click + New column.
Display name:
First Seen
Description:
Timestamp when Flow 1 first encountered this Org Unit string in a LeanIX export.
Data type: Date and Time
Format: Date and time
Required: Optional
Under Advanced options, set the Schema name to:
firstseen
Click Save.

Step 9 — Add column: Affected Records
Click + New column.
Display name:
Affected Records
Description:
Count of Application records currently using this Org Unit string. Updated by Flow 1 each cycle.
Data type: Whole Number
Minimum value:
0
Required: Optional
Under Advanced options, set the Schema name to:
affectedrecords
Click Save.

Step 10 — Add Alternate Key on Org Unit Variant
In table editor → Keys area → + New key.
Display name:
Org Unit Variant Unique
Columns: select Org Unit Variant
Click Save. (Background job runs ~30-60 sec; key shows "Active" when done.)
